# 01-data-cleaning.ipynb â€” Data cleaning

1. Setup
   - imports (pandas, numpy, matplotlib/seaborn, pathlib)
   - set working directory (Path(...))
   - load raw CSV(s)

2. Inspect raw data
   - df.head(), df.info(), df.describe()
   - value counts for categorical columns
   - check missing values: df.isna().sum()

3. Cleaning steps
   - drop duplicates: df.drop_duplicates(subset='video_id', inplace=True)
   - parse dates: df['publish_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['publish_date'])
   - convert numeric columns: df['views'] = pd.to_numeric(...)
   - fill missing comments with 0, or impute where appropriate

4. Feature engineering
   - df['days_since_upload'] = (today - publish_date).dt.days
   - df['view_rate'] = df['views'] / df['days_since_upload']
   - df['title_length'] = df['title'].str.len()
   - extract publish month/year/day_of_week

5. Save processed data
   - df.to_csv('data/processed/videos_clean.csv', index=False)
